    "actor_description": "Something swells in my chest—sudden and clean, like breath filling a space I didn't know was empty. My spine lengthens before I choose it; my shoulders pull back. Attention narrows to a point, sharp and generous at once. No hunger in it. No measuring myself against what I'm seeing. Just yes—recognition that lands warm and sure. My ribs expand around it. This matters. This is worth holding.",
    "description_text": "{actor} goes quiet mid-breath, their gaze sharpening on a fixed point. Their chest rises—shoulders drawing back, spine lengthening—as if pulled upright by invisible thread. Their face opens: eyebrows lift slightly, jaw unclenches. The quality of their stillness shifts from passive to magnetic, attention condensed to a single bright line.",
    "alternate_descriptions": {
        "auditory": "I hear a quick inhale—air catching high in the chest—then silence that feels deliberate. When speech returns, the voice steadies, precision replacing casual rhythm. Each word carries weight now, like the speaker knows something matters.",
        "tactile": "The air tightens as someone leans forward—a shift you feel before you see. Their stillness becomes denser, charged. The space between you shrinks without movement, as if focus itself has mass and just contracted the distance.",
        "limited": "I sense a pause—sharp, deliberate—followed by attention locking into place. The quality of their presence changes: heavier, clearer, aimed."
    },
